The paper deals with discovering hidden groups and their structure from streaming interaction data, which involves analyzing social networks and communication patterns. This falls under the scope of social network analysis, data mining, and natural language processing, which are covered by the sub-categories of cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.DB, and cs.CL. Among these, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering) are the most likely categories, as they directly relate to the problem of discovering hidden groups in social networks and developing algorithms for analyzing interaction data. The other categories are also relevant, as they involve aspects such as database management, computational linguistics, and machine learning, which are important for processing and analyzing large-scale interaction data.
